      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPRING DROP (4) missed the frame last time but before three back recorded the quickest win (25.89) on the program at Temora in a Grade 5. Meets a moderate line up and rates on top this time. CONFUSION REIGNS (2) placed on debut then improved with a 4 length win (30.18) at Wentworth Park over 520m. Nicely drawn here. Harder here but will be in this for a long way. HELLO SHELLY (1) has mixed form recently, finishing fifth (30.27) in a Grade 5 at Nowra latest but did run well two back when in the frame. Well placed here and should do much better. JIGSAW BILLY (8) is among the chances again if she runs up to the latest effort.",
